robot

Class ObjectDetector

  • java.lang.Object
    • robot.ObjectDetector

  • public class ObjectDetector
extends java.lang.Object
    The object detector class is responsible for using the ultrasonic sensor and the light sensor to detect objects in front of the robot.
    Version:
    2.5
    Author:
    Shawn Lu, Solvie Lee

    • Constructor Detail

      • ObjectDetector

        public ObjectDetector(Navigator navi,
                      SampleProvider usValue,
                      float[] usData,
                      SampleProvider colorSensor,
                      float[] colorData,
                      SampleProvider colorSensor2,
                      float[] colorData2,
                      boolean autostart)
        Default constructor
        Parameters:
        navi - the Navigator
        usValue - the ultrasonic sensor
        usData - the data from the ultrasonic sensor
        colorSensor - the forwards facing color sensor
        colorData - the data from the forwards facing color sensor
        colorSensor2 - the downwards facing color sensor
        colorData2 - the data from the downwards facing color sensor
        autostart - whether the ObjectDetector should autostart

    • Method Detail

      • timedOut

        public void timedOut()
        This method checks the sensor data whenever it is called, and puts it through the filter. It also tells the navigator whether an object/flag was seen or not.

      • getdistance

        public int getdistance()
        A method to get the raw distance detected by the ultrasonic sensor.
        Returns:
        raw distance in cm.

      • updateNavi

        public void updateNavi(double farDist,
                       double closeishDist,
                       double closeDist)
        This method allows the object detector to tell the navigator the state of the field of vision.
        Parameters:
        farDist - Distance within which the object detector will say an object has been detected
        closeishDist - Distance within which the object detector will say that an object is somewhat close ("closeish")
        closeDist - Distance within which the object detector will say an object is close

      • getVisionStatus

        public boolean[] getVisionStatus()
        This method allows outside classes to get all the information from the objectDetector, whether an object was seen, and whether it's close.
        Returns:
        array of boolean values that say (index 0) if an object was detected in front of the robot, and (index 1), if the object detected is close
